The Pastor of the Citadel Global Community Church, Tunde Bakare has declared his intention to run for the 2023 presidency. Daily Post reports that Bakare disclosed this on Saturday at the virtual meeting unveiling Project 16 to Nigerians in diaspora with the theme The portrait of a new Nigeria, organized by the PTB4Nigeria in diaspora group. Bakare urged Nigerians to consider the capacity of candidates before electing a leader in 2023. The cleric warned that ahead of the 2023 general elections, the south is being set against the north, while Christians are set against Muslims. He said, “The PTB brand is a rallying point for all Nigerians. I have a vision of a new Nigeria and I will play a leading role as we approach the Nigeria of our dreams.”